modules.description: This module generates ULIDs (Universally Unique Lexicographically Sortable Identifiers) using time and randomness, providing functions to encode timestamps and random values into Base32, increment Base32 strings, and create ULID generation functions with optional custom PRNGs. It operates on integers for time and randomness, producing string-based ULIDs. Use cases include generating unique, time-ordered identifiers for distributed systems, logs, or databases without collisions.
